In terms of applications, the food and beverages segment is dominating the market, driven by the increasing popularity of functional foods and drinks that offer added health benefits. Consumers are seeking products that not only taste good but also provide nutritional value, leading to a surge in demand for health ingredients in the food and beverage industry. Additionally, the pharmaceuticals, dietary supplements, and personal care products segments are also experiencing growth as consumers look for wellness products that cater to their specific health needs.

The source of health ingredients is another key segmentation factor, with plant-based ingredients witnessing significant growth as consumers prioritize natural and organic products. Plant-based sources are perceived as healthier and more sustainable options, aligning with the growing sustainability movement in the food and beverage industry. Companies are focusing on sourcing high-quality plant-based ingredients to meet consumer preferences and sustainability standards, driving innovation and product development in the market.

